      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is certainly possible that the higher-ups are intentionally limiting your view to maintain operational stability and protect proprietary business models. By focusing strictly on \"input accuracy,\" they are managing the risk by ensuring the foundation is solid, without needing employees to grasp the full, volatile implications of the complex downstream reactions. This compartmentalization is common in large, powerful organizations to prevent single points of failure or unauthorized knowledge proliferation.",
